The value of exportString should not be set as follows:

```
    public DemoModel(IProject project) {
        super(project);
        exportString = "Export to Demo input format";

        // TODO: (optional) Add User Code Here
    }
```

The problem is that exportString will be null until after the super constructor is called. This means that when Item.setupItemInfo() is called to add exportString to the list allowed actions, it will add a null value to the list.

This should just be set in Item.setupItemInfo() as such:

```
    @Override
    protected void setupItemInfo() {
        setName("Demo Model");
        setDescription("Specify information about Demo");
        exportString = "Export to Demo input format";
        allowedActions.add(0, exportString);
    }
```

The IOService is injected by the OSGI framework and should never be committed in client code. The following lines in the setupForm() operation from a generated Item should not be there:

```
        if (ioService == null) {
            setIOService(new IOService());
            ioService = getIOService();
        }
```

Newly generated Items are returning null in process(), but they should say

return status;

to return the status of the Item.
